## 🏗 Phase 1 — Foundation & Core Loop *(Weeks 1–3)*

**Goal:** A working, deployable skeleton where a user can sign up, read a prompt, record/write, and see a "processing" state. The full AI pipeline does **not** need to be live — just the structure.

### What Gets Built

#### Infrastructure & DevOps
- Docker Compose for **local dev** (FastAPI + PostgreSQL + Redis + Celery worker + flower)
- `Makefile` targets: `make dev`, `make migrate`, `make test`, `make lint`
- GitHub Actions CI: lint (ruff, mypy, eslint), test (pytest), build check
- Environment config: `.env.local` (dev) → Vercel/Render env vars (prod)
- `pre-commit` hooks: black, ruff, mypy, eslint

#### Backend — FastAPI
- Project scaffold: `app/core/config.py` (pydantic-settings), `app/core/deps.py` (DB session, current user)
- SQLAlchemy 2.0 async models + Alembic migrations for ALL core tables
- Clerk JWT middleware (`app/core/security.py`) — validate token on every protected route
- Health check endpoint: `GET /health` → returns DB + Redis status
- API routes:
  - `GET /speaking/tasks` — list all 8 tasks with metadata
  - `POST /speaking/attempts/start` — create attempt record, return `attempt_id`
  - `POST /speaking/attempts/{id}/upload-audio` — return pre-signed S3 URL
  - `GET /writing/tasks` — list tasks
  - `POST /writing/attempts/start` — create attempt record
  - `POST /writing/attempts/{id}/submit` — save essay text, enqueue job
  - `GET /attempts/{id}/status` — polling endpoint (`pending|processing|complete|failed`)
- **Usage quota check** at attempt creation: reject free users over daily limit

#### Background Workers (Celery)
- Celery app wired to Redis broker
- `speaking_worker` task stub: receives `attempt_id`, logs receipt, updates status to `processing` (real AI later)
- `writing_worker` task stub: same pattern
- Flower monitoring dashboard on port 5555 (dev only)

#### Frontend — Next.js
- Initial layout: global nav, auth guards via Clerk `<SignedIn>/<SignedOut>`
- Route scaffolding: all routes exist with placeholder content
- **Speaking practice flow** (full UX, no AI yet):
  - Task selection grid
  - Instruction screen with task description
  - Countdown: 3 → 2 → 1 → GO
  - Preparation timer (countdown bar)
  - Auto-start recording via `MediaRecorder API`
  - Response timer (countdown bar, progresses to 0)
  - Auto-stop + upload audio to S3 pre-signed URL
  - Immediately POST to `/speaking/attempts/{id}/submit-audio` to trigger worker
  - Show "Analyzing your response..." skeleton with polled status
- **Writing practice flow:**
  - Instruction screen + countdown
  - Rich textarea with live word/char count
  - Auto-submit at timer end
  - "Analyzing..." skeleton state
- Shared components: `CountdownTimer`, `ProgressBar`, `AttemptCard`, `StatusBadge`

#### Admin (Lightweight CMS)
- Clerk-role gated `/admin` route
- CRUD UI for `speaking_prompts` and `writing_prompts`
- Seed script: 8 speaking prompts + 2 writing prompts on migration

### Phase 1 Deliverable
> A user can sign up, attempt a speaking or writing task, upload their response, and see a persistent "processing" state — the full UX loop minus AI feedback. CI passes. All infra runs in Docker locally.

