## 🧪 Phase 4 — Mock Tests, Analytics & Hardening *(Weeks 10–12)*

**Goal:** Full CELPIP-style mock tests, advanced analytics, admin tooling, and production hardening.

### What Gets Built

#### Mock Test System
- `mock_tests` table: test session with ordered prompt sequence
- **Speaking Mock Test**: Tasks 1–8, sequential, strict timer, no ability to skip/go back
- **Writing Mock Test**: Task 1 + Task 2, sequential
- `POST /mock-tests/start` → creates session
- `GET /mock-tests/{id}/next-task` → returns next prompt in sequence
- Final report aggregates all task scores into overall session estimate
- Mock test UI: full-screen, distraction-free mode; no nav; progress indicator (Task X of 8)

#### Timed Section Practice
- New mode, similar to mock test but scoped to individual module
- Speaking section (Tasks 1–8), Writing section (Task 1 + 2)
- Same strict flow as real exam

#### Analytics (Admin + User-facing)
- Admin analytics endpoint: cohort data, average bands by signup date, retention
- User analytics: `/progress/analytics` — band velocity (slope), consistency score, projected target date
- Admin dashboard CMS enhancements:
  - Prompt quality metrics (average scores per prompt)
  - Failed jobs monitor (link to Flower)
  - User lookup (search by email, view plan + history)

#### Performance & Reliability Hardening
- **Rate limiting**: `slowapi` on FastAPI — per-user and per-IP
- **Request timeout**: `asyncio.wait_for` on AI calls, fall back to `failed` status
- **Dead-letter queue**: failed Celery tasks → DLQ, retry 3x, then alert
- **Structured logging**: `structlog` → JSON logs → log aggregator (e.g., Datadog, Grafana Loki)
- **Metrics**: Prometheus metrics endpoint (`/metrics`) — attempt latency, queue depth, AI cost/attempt
- **DB connection pooling**: asyncpg pool tuned for concurrent load
- **S3 lifecycle rules**: delete audio files after 30 days (configurable)
- **Full test suite**: pytest-asyncio for all API routes, mock AI provider, 80%+ coverage target

#### Security Hardening
- OWASP checklist per route
- Signed S3 URLs (15-min expiry for upload, 1-hour for download)
- `Content-Security-Policy` header on Next.js
- Row-level security: users can only access own attempts (enforced in SQL, not just app layer)
- Clerk webhook signature verification

### Phase 4 Deliverable
> Full feature mock tests, advanced analytics, hardened for production traffic with observability and security controls in place.

